            <h1>Odin Recipes</h1>
            <a href="recieps/pasta.html"> Lasagna Recipe </a>
            </div>

            <img src="https://www.lastingredient.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/rigatoni-noodles-with-tomato-sauce.jpg" alt="Pasta">
            <p>This wonderful pasta will make anyone's mouth water</p>
            <p>This recipe follows a great trendy meal option with a twist of lemon and garlic</p>

        <div class="pad">   
            <div class="text"> 
                <h4>Ingredients</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Tomatoes 300g</li>
                <li>Spaghetti</li>
                <li>Oregano</li>
                <li>Vegetable Stock 500ml</li>
                <li>Muscles / Clams 500g</li>
                <li>Lemons x3</li>
                <li>1 Cup Wine</li>
                <li>Basil</li>
                <li>1 Tsp Oil</li>
                <li>2 Onions White</li>
                <li>Black Pepper & Salt</li>
            </ul>

                <h3>Steps to Prepare</h3>

            <ol>
                <li>Par-cook the muscles in garlic, butter and lemon juice for 10mins until they begin to open, place to the side</li>
                <li>Chop onions & tomatoes, place into pan with 1tsp of oil on low heat</li>
                <li>Add to the veggies your tomatoes, puree and veggie stock</li>
                <li>Add in 1tsp salt, 1tsp pepper & a generous pinch of Oregano, add wine and cook down</li>
                <li>Add the spaghetti to a pot and allow to boil while the sauce nears completion</li>
                <li>Add in muscles which were set to the side, you can add in clam meat to add more depth to the meal </li>
                <li>Allow the sauce to complete when oils and fats rise to the top, add in a 1/4 cup of pasta water as well as the spaghetti which should be aldente.</li>
                <li>Serve while fresh and hot, add Basil to the pasta to add a nice finish to the meal</li>
            </ol>
            </div>
        </div>

